('m042', 'Y', 'M 42', 'NGC 1976', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Orion Nebula', 'M42 Orion Nebula NGC 1976', 'ngc1976.jpg', 'ngc1976_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'Nikon D50', 'GSO 8 RC', 'EQ6-Pro', 'WO Megrez 72FD, PHD, QHY5', 'No flats or darks. ISO 800', 'Donvale', '2009-12-07', 'The Orion Nebula  (NGC 1976) is a diffuse nebula situated south of Orion''s Belt. Distance is only 1,344 light years. I really need to do this one again.', 'ngc1976_annotated.jpg', 'None', '83.755640652021', '-5.465681181480', '1.006818659614', '0.509811118015', '3059.721906567668', '2027.732780463074', '50.995365109461', '33.795546341051', '89.951683688400', 'y'),
('m078', '', 'M 78', 'NGC 2068', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'M78 (NGC 2068)', 'ngc2068.jpg', 'ngc2068_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'QHY9', 'GSO 8 RC', 'EQ6-Pro', 'WO Megrez 72FD, PHD, QHY5 Drift (-9,-51) over 1:05', 'LRGB 50:25:30:25, total 2:10 (subs 5min) @ -20C First 4 Subs at 10C', 'Donvale', '2010-02-18', 'Messier 78 (also known as NGC 2068) is a reflection nebula in the constellation Orion about 1,600 light years from Earth. NGC 2071 can be seen to the top right, NGC 2064 to the lower left and NGC 2067 just beow and to the right of M78 which is the bright area in the center. Warm night (19.7C at 01:00) No moon, clouds came in at 1am. Image needs reprocessing.', 'ngc2068_annotated.jpg', 'None', '86.708286301413', '0.110330753930', '0.699437614637', '0.381457324282', '2217.916676013720', '1619.897515499140', '36.965277933562', '26.998291924986', '275.261946648209', 'y'),
