('rcw078', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 78', '', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 78', 'rcw78.jpg', 'rcw78_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'STL-11000M', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', '10 Sec Selfguide', 'Ha 60', 'Donvale', '2015-05-19', 'RCW 78 is a ring nebula around the Wolf-Rayet star WR 55 in the constellation Centaurus.', 'rcw78_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '203.491229525309', '-62.255221545114', '1.602222819084', '1.071935244812', '6421.709058889690', '4281.139372593130', '107.028484314828', '71.352322876552', '88.451280985721', 'y'),
('rcw105ha', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 105', '', '', 'Gum 51', '', '', 'RCW 105 / Gum 51', 'rcw105ha.jpg', 'rcw105ha_thumb.jpg', 'Cluster', 'STL-11000M', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 10sec', 'Ha 160', 'Donvale', '2015-05-18', 'RCW 105 also known as Gum 51 is an emission nebula in the constellation Norma.', 'rcw105ha_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '242.660538050430', '-49.154605864379', '1.602918201578', '1.002277735445', '5873.092290580873', '4193.234015327392', '97.884871509681', '69.887233588790', '88.099901879140', 'y'),
('rcw059', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 59', '', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 59', 'rcw59.jpg', 'rcw59_thumb.jpg', 'Supernova Remnant', 'STL-11000M', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide, 10 sec, Bin 2x2', '2x20 Min HA (Mosaic)', 'Donvale', '2015-05-19', 'RCW 59 is believed to be a supernova remnant. The filaments extend over a huge 3 degree loop - only part is shown in this image.', 'na', '3 KORRW', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'f'),
('rcw062', 'Y', '', '', 'IC 2944', 'RCW 62', '', '', 'Gum 42', '', 'Running Chicken', 'RCW 62 Running Chicken', 'rcw62.jpg', 'rcw62_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'STL-11000M', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', '5 Sec Selfguide', '18*10 mins = 180 mins = 3:00 Ha', 'Donvale', '2017-03-07', 'Central area of the Running Chicken Nebula, also known as IC 2944, RCW 62 and Gum 42. Lambda Centauri (HD 100841, HIP 56561) is the bright star in the upper right of the image and is actually much closer to us at 380 ly than the Nebula.', 'rcw62_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'f'),
('ngc1968', '', '', 'NGC 1968', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NGC 1968 in LMC', 'ngc1968.jpg', 'ngc1968_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 3 sec', 'H:O:S 80:90:50 min @5 min subs, 3:40 total. -10C', 'Donvale', '2025-01-12', 'Cosmic reefs area in the LMC. Includes NGC 1968, NGC 1955, NCG 1974 (Left side) and NGC 2004 (lower centre) and NGC 2020, NGC 2014, NGC 2021, NCG 2011, NGC 2030, NGC 2032, NGC 2035, NGC 2040 (right hand side)', 'ngc1968_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '82.685502318906', '-67.468467500897', '0.684923201161', '0.675725447818', '4062.279506087120', '2677.364793339160', '67.704658434785', '44.622746555653', '180.022184420461', 'y'),
('rcw033', 'Y', '', '', '', 'RCW 33', '', '', 'Gum 17', '', '', 'RCW 33', 'rcw33.jpg', 'rcw33_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'STL-11000M', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', '5 sec MaximDL', 'Ha 11 x 10min = 1:50', 'Donvale', '2017-03-06', 'RCW 33 also called Gum 17 is an extensive emission nebula visible in the constellation of Vela.', 'rcw33_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '132.834411965355', '-42.166471951282', '1.603861362951', '1.073031479930', '6428.276342708711', '4285.517561805807', '107.137939045145', '71.425292696763', '266.401289215418', 'y'),
('rcw007', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 7', 'Sh2-302', '', 'Gum 6', 'LBN 1046', 'Snowman Nebula', 'RCW 7 Snowman Nebula', 'rcw7.jpg', 'rcw7_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', '4 sec selfguide N.I.N.A. & PHD2', 'Ha:O:S @ 5 mins subs 115:65:100 Total 4:40', 'Donvale', '2025-01-18', 'RCW 7 (Sh2-302, Gum 6, LBN 1046), sometimes referred to as the Snowman Nebula, with emissions due to ionization by the open star cluster Bochum 5 in the constellation Puppis.', 'rcw7_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '112.910440392555', '-17.043931993049', '0.684946620637', '0.666842577818', '3948.032321354200', '2732.252069722740', '65.800538689237', '45.537534495379', '359.234541989085', 'y'),
('rcw019', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 19', '', '', 'Gum 10', '', '', 'RCW 19', 'rcw19.jpg', 'rcw19_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'TOA130NS', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide N.I.N.A. & PHD2', 'S:H:O 190:140:165: Total 8:25', 'Donvale', '2025-01-22', 'Gum 10 (also known as RCW 19) is an emission nebula located in the constellation Puppis. RCW 20 is also at the top left of the picture. Taken over 2 nights. Combined as SHO image in Pixinsight with BlurXterminator & NoiseXterminator.', 'rcw19_annotated.jpg', '67F', '124.174168063893', '-35.879509106042', '0.773036218370', '0.798616821793', '4787.413300365400', '3184.909219684390', '79.790221672757', '53.081820328073', '359.998602043577', 'y'),
('rcw062b', '', '', '', 'IC 2944', 'RCW 62', '', '', 'Gum 42', '', 'Running Chicken', 'RCW 62 Running Chicken', 'rcw62b.jpg', 'rcw62b_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'H:S:O 8:8:8 * 5 min exposures = 120 mins = 2:00 ', 'Donvale', '2025-01-17', 'This is the body part of the Running Chicken Nebula, also known as IC 2944, RCW 62 and Gum 42. Lambda Centaurus is the bright star in the upper right of the image.', 'rcw62b_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '174.577776056239', '-63.373019249732', '0.685040286026', '0.712276321996', '4259.580498507990', '2855.932952441270', '70.993008308467', '47.598882540688', '359.505690520334', 'y'),
('ngc3199', '', '', 'NGC 3199', '', 'RCW 48', '', '', 'GUM 28', '', 'Banana Nebula', 'NGC 3199 RCW 48 Banana Nebula', 'ngc3199.jpg', 'ngc3199_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide @ 4 sec', 'SHO 72:76:75 @ 5 min exposures, total 18:25 @ -10C over 5 nights', 'Donvale', '2025-02-26', 'NGC 3199 (also known as GUM 28, RCW 48) is an emission nebula in the constellation Carina. It is commonly known as the Banana Nebula. The object was discovered in 1826 by the Scottish astronomer James Dunlop. In the top left you can also see a bubble planetary nebula (PK283-01.2 aka MeWe 1-2). 18 hour image taken over 5 nights.', 'ngc3199_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '154.201942389720', '-57.985677405087', '0.670899686336', '0.670645313553', '4009.296525543200', '2690.978641893200', '66.821608759053', '44.849644031553', '179.812619463838', 'y'),
('rcw060', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 60', '', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 60', 'rcw60.jpg', 'rcw60_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide, 4 sec', 'S:H:O 25:40:22 @5 min exposures 7:15 total @-10C over 2 nights', 'Donvale', '2025-02-12', 'RCW 60 is part of the Lambda Centaurus nebula complex (centered around RCW 62). This is actually 2  distinct nebulae at different distances: Gum 39 and Gum 40. Also includes IC 2872. RCW 60 is located around 13000 light years from Earth. Taken over 2 nights 12-Feb and 16-Feb 2025.', 'rcw60_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '172.189396640635', '-62.747077579713', '0.671257101527', '0.692858277766', '4165.150314974870', '2745.441545245320', '69.419171916248', '45.757359087422', '90.562052822687', 'y'),
('ngc3576b', '', '', 'NGC 3576', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Statue of Liberty Nebula', 'NGC 3576 Statue of Liberty Nebula', 'ngc3576b.jpg', 'ngc3576b_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 4 sec', 'SHO 125:150:145 Total 7:00', 'Donvale', '2025-02-20', 'NGC 3576 & NGC 3579 (on the right hand side of this image) is an Emission nebula about 9,000 light-years away in the constellation of Carina. Now known as \"The Statue of Liberty Nebula\". On the left hand side can been seen NGC 3603. Processed in Pixinsight as Foraxx.', 'ngc3576b_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '168.366377041964', '-61.245619501750', '0.671013121243', '0.694226148081', '4162.965404191360', '2766.587098884750', '69.382756736523', '46.109784981412', '358.593546365120', 'y'),
('ngc3503', '', '', 'NGC 3503', '', 'RCW 54', '', '', 'Gum 34a', '', '', 'NGC 3503', 'ngc3503.jpg', 'ngc3503_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Self guide 4sec', 'H:O:S 140:130:120 mins, 5 min exposures @-10C total 6:30', 'Donvale', '2025-02-23', 'NGC 3503 is a small reflection and can been seen as the bright area right in the center of this image. The wide field nebulosity is part of RCW 54. The area imaged is located about midway between Eta Carina NGC 3372 (to the right) and the Statue of Liberty Nebula NGC 3576 (to the lower left). Interestingly it lies almost exactly on the galactic equator. Gum 34a and Gum 34b are also in the field of this image.', 'ngc3503_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '165.369188278365', '-59.828881179559', '0.671122877110', '0.694106316160', '4157.606223698110', '2773.079728219630', '69.293437061635', '46.217995470327', '179.314154767281', 'y'),
('ngc3532', '', '', 'NGC 3532', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Wishing Well Cluster', 'NGC 3532 Wishing Well Cluster', 'ngc3532.jpg', 'ngc3532_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Self guide 4sec', 'H:O:S 100:75:16 mins, 5 min exposures @-10C total 4:15', 'Donvale', '2025-02-24', 'NGC 3532 (Caldwell 91) with many names including the Wishing Well Cluster is an open cluster some 1320 light years from Earth in the constellation Carina. Its population of approximately 150 stars of 7th magnitude or fainter includes seven red giants and seven white dwarfs.', 'ngc3532_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '166.408424745231', '-58.751661500903', '0.671422514341', '0.697830352855', '4182.290841828810', '2784.389166971280', '69.704847363814', '46.406486116188', '359.812276875575', 'y'),
('ngc3247', '', '', 'NGC 3247', '', 'RCW 49', '', '', '', '', '', 'NGC 3247 RCW 49', 'ngc3247.jpg', 'ngc3247_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide @ 4 sec', 'SHO 125:140:85, total 5:50 @ -10C with 5 min exposures', 'Donvale', '2025-02-25', 'NGC 3247 also known as RCW 49, is a H II region nebula located 13,700 light years away. Commonly known as the Whirling Dervish Nebula. The bright star in this image is HD 90772 or V399 Carinae which is 206 times bigger than the sun and is 7000 ly away.', 'ngc3247_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '156.061100349511', '-57.765218776802', '0.670991257242', '0.693531095495', '4157.461829874400', '2765.825962353500', '69.291030497907', '46.097099372558', '179.976726724557', 'y'),
('n70b', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N70 Superbubble', 'n70b.jpg', 'n70b_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', '4 Sec self guided', '25 x 5 min x 4 Ha, 2:05 total exposure', 'Donvale', '2025-01-03', 'Henize 70 (also known as N70 and DEM301) is a luminous Superbubble of interstellar gas about 300 light-years in diameter, blown by winds from hot, massive stars and supernova explosions. Also in this image are N71, N73 and N74. This is my first test image with a new camera - ASI2600MM Pro Duo.', 'n70b_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '86.231267621706', '-67.668933163060', '0.684794921879', '0.711704195148', '4270.381132838240', '2832.311796892070', '71.173018880637', '47.205196614868', '258.517834060285', 'y'),
('rcw035', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 35', '', '', 'GUM 18', '', '', 'RCW 35 & GUM 18', 'rcw35.jpg', 'rcw35_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', '4 sec selfguide', 'H:S:O 47:38:32 @ 5 min exposures = 9:45 total @-10C over 4 nights', 'Donvale', '2025-02-11', 'RCW 35 (also called Gum 18) is a stunning HII region in the Vela constellation.', 'rcw35_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '133.096486201366', '-43.703362454607', '0.773215008035', '0.727684595262', '4554.236397326362', '2590.270276917371', '75.903939955439', '43.171171281956', '95.684312584335', 'y'),
('ngc2736', '', '', 'NGC 2736', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Pencil Nebula', 'NGC 2736 Pencil Nebula', 'ngc2736.jpg', 'ngc2736_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 4 sec', 'HSO 22:20:20 @5 min exposures total 5:10 @-10C ', 'Donvale', '2025-02-11', 'NGC 2736 (also known as the Pencil Nebula) is a small part of the Vela Supernova Remnant. It resides about 815 light-years from Earth.', 'ngc2736_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '134.894748714053', '-46.057241558157', '0.671214386422', '0.674783625476', '4018.560531509780', '2730.500123965550', '66.976008858496', '45.508335399426', '90.171446635999', 'y'),
('ngc4945b', '', '', 'NGC 4945', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NGC 4945', 'ngc4945b.jpg', 'ngc4945b_thumb.jpg', 'Galaxy', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 4 sec', 'LRGB 24:22:16:20 @5min exposures total 6:50 @-10C', 'Donvale', '2025-03-04', 'NGC 4945 is a dusty, edge-on spiral galaxy in the constellation Centaurus. Distance is approx 11.7 million light years. Other galaxies that can been seen are NGC 4976 (35 million LY) and NGC 4945A.', 'ngc4945b_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '196.369657110256', '-49.462691419457', '0.670805302209', '0.693674488233', '4155.638847185850', '2770.425898123900', '69.260647453098', '46.173764968732', '359.635541637024', 'y'),
('ngc2997', '', '', 'NGC 2997', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NGC 2997', 'ngc2997.jpg', 'ngc2997_thumb.jpg', 'Galaxy', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 4 sec', 'HaLRGB 10:5:10:10:6 @5min exposures total 3:25 @-10C', 'Donvale', '2025-03-06', 'NGC 2997 is a face-on unbarred spiral galaxy about 40 million light-years away in the constellation of Antlia', 'ngc2997_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '146.410664930320', '-31.191179525530', '0.671010356548', '0.695420839877', '4180.394521293660', '2755.839534342390', '69.673242021561', '45.930658905706', '179.367186360954', 'y'),
('rcw061', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 61', '', '', '', '', 'Running Chicken nebula', 'RCW 61', 'rcw61.jpg', 'rcw61_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'TOA130NS', 'EQ6-Pro', 'Selfguide, 4 sec', 'H:O:S 54:48:39 @2 min and 19:19:10 @5 min exposures. Total 9:27 at -10C', 'Heathcote', '2025-03-08', 'RCW 61 forms the feet of the Running Chicken nebula complex. Taken over 2 nights at the ASV dark sky site.', 'rcw61_annotated.jpg', '67F', '172.592342695962', '-63.818457991889', '0.773057654305', '0.791044989248', '4738.843420892274', '3159.486633146284', '78.980723681538', '52.658110552438', '91.817562471031', 'y'),
('ngc3372b', '', '', 'NGC 3372', '', 'RCW 53', '', '', '', '', 'Eta Carinae Nebula', 'NGC 3372 Eta Carinae Nebula', 'ngc3372b.jpg', 'ngc3372b_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 4 sec', 'SHO 75:84:81 Total 20 hours @-10C 5 min exposures', 'Donvale', '2025-03-20', 'NGC 3372 or The Eta Carinae Nebula is an emission nebula in the constellation Carina. It is located about about 7500 ly from Earth. This is an 8 panel mosaic with a field of view about 2 x 2.5 degrees.', 'ngc3372b_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'f'),
('rcw080', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 80', '', '', 'Gum 48d', '', '', 'RCW 80 Gum 48d', 'rcw80.jpg', 'rcw80_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 4 sec', 'S:H:O 84:74:80 * 5 min exposures @-10C = 19:50 total', 'Donvale', '2025-03-24', 'RCW 80 (Gum 48d) is an HII region ionised by the supergiant star HR 5171B. The cluster of four bright stars in a line at the bottom is NGC 5281 - the Little Scorpion Cluster.', 'rcw80_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '206.120000000000', '-62.638734845009', '0.671234761610', '0.600179132452', '3574.325105573970', '2428.527367505470', '59.572085092900', '40.475456125091', '359.961413324048', 'y'),
('ngc2080', '', '', 'NGC 2080', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Ghost Head Nebula', 'NGC 2080 Ghost Head Nebula', 'ngc2080.jpg', 'ngc2080_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide PHD2', 'H:O:S 24:24:23 5 min exposures at -10C Total 5:55', 'Donvale', '2025-10-28', 'NGC 2080, also known as the Ghost Head Nebula, is a star-forming region and emission nebula close to the Tarantula nebula, in the constellation Dorado. It belongs to the Large Magellanic Cloud. Also contains IC 2145, NGC 2052, NGC 2033, NGC 2074, NGC 2081,  NGC 2050. First image after a long break.', 'ngc2080_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '85.126246315319', '-69.664238771950', '0.671096412049', '0.696147255927', '4168.179815237585', '2783.707917180084', '69.469663587293', '46.395131953001', '0.754571319951', 'y'),
('n11', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'N11 Bean Nebula', 'n11.jpg', 'n11_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'H:O:S 17:20:20 at 5 min exposures -10C = 4:45', 'Donvale', '2025-10-29', 'N11 is the brightest emission nebula in the north-west part of the Large Magellanic Cloud in the Dorado constellation. This image also includes IC 2115, IC 2116, NGC 1733, NGC 1760, NGC 1761, NGC 1763, NGC 1769, NGC 1773 and NGC 1776.  Also of interest is N11L at the 3 O''Clock position - a supernova remnant within the N11 complex that is part of a two-stage starburst process.', 'n11_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '74.216050658244', '-66.406119796367', '0.671216544273', '0.691131263670', '4150.803109783996', '2744.604449532141', '69.180051829733', '45.743407492202', '1.994323988397', 'y'),
('ngc2327', '', '', 'NGC 2327', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Seagull Nebula', 'NGC 2327 Seagull Nebula (part)', 'ngc2327.jpg', 'ngc2327_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'H:S:O 95:80:95 min @5 min subs, 4:30 total @-10C', 'Donvale', '2026-01-11', 'NGC 2327 is a Reflection Nebula in the Canis Major and is a component of the larger Seagull Nebula. Processed as Foraxx.', 'ngc2327_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '106.033510300961', '-11.316689916218', '0.670887689003', '0.698514873382', '4185.668291687275', '2788.209235494841', '69.761138194788', '46.470153924914', '1.445691365027', 'y'),
('velasnr', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Vela SNR', 'Vela SNR G263.9-03.3', 'velasnr.jpg', 'velasnr_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'H:S:O 480:455:430 min @5 min subs, 22:45 total @-10C', 'Donvale', '2026-01-01', '3 panel mosaic of the a small part of the Vela supernova remnant (SNR G263.9-03.3). Taken over 5 nights. Size: 1.13 x 1.97 deg, Pixel scale: 0.671 arcsec/pixel\r\n', 'na', '3 KORRW', '127.844028773770', '-43.698206708357', '0.671116166154', '1.132734932744', '4050.186062739218', '7078.933320592091', '67.503101045654', '117.982222009868', '181.163398625325', 'y'),
('rcw040b', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 40', '', '', 'Gum 25', '', '', 'RCW 40 (Gum 25) RCW 39 ', 'rcw40b.jpg', 'rcw40b_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide 4 sec', 'S:H:O 170:200:140 * 5 min exposures @-10C = 8:30 total taken over 2 nights', 'Donvale', '2026-01-23', 'RCW 40 (also know as GUM 25) is a HII region in Vela. Also includes RCW 39. Processed as SHO taken over 2 nights 12 & 23 Jan 2026. ', 'rcw40b_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, ''),
('rcw014', '', '', 'NGC 2367', '', 'RCW 14', '', '', '', 'LBN 1054', '', 'RCW 14', 'rcw14.jpg', 'rcw14_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'S:H:O: 105:120:120 min @5 min subs, 5:45 total @-10C', 'Donvale', '2026-01-14', 'RCW 14 (also known as LBN 1054) is part of the GS234-02 supershell in the constellation Canis Major. The main ionising star is the O8 V star HD 57236. Includes star cluster NGC 2367. Processed as SHO.\r\n', 'rcw14_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '109.784490339620', '-21.928915079117', '0.671112473970', '0.698231899679', '4181.701825308542', '2790.485666768242', '69.695030421809', '46.508094446137', '181.531070483314', 'y'),
('ngc2244', '', '', 'NGC 2244', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Rosette Nebula', 'NGC 2244 Rosette Nebula', 'ngc2244.jpg', 'ngc2244_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'S:H:O 80:90:85 mins @5 min exposures @-10C total 4:15 hours', 'Donvale', '2026-01-17', 'The Rosette Nebula is a large, circular H II region. Distance is 5,200 light years. Also includes NGC 2237, NGC 2246, NGC 2238, Sh2-275, NGC 2239, LBN 948, LBN 949.', 'ngc2244_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '97.941237142430', '4.998134785642', '0.671096444693', '0.697104073993', '4179.588657550499', '2779.010377475372', '69.659810959175', '46.316839624590', '181.682868709719', 'y'),
('ngc2359', '', '', 'NGC 2359', 'IC 468', 'RCW 5', 'Sh2-298', '', 'Gum 4', '', 'Thor''s Helmet', 'NGC 2359 Thor''s Helmet', 'ngc2359.jpg', 'ngc2359_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Self guided', 'S:H:O 120:130:120 mins total 6:10 @ 5 min exposures @-10C ', 'Donvale', '2026-01-18', 'NGC 2359 (also known as Thor''s Helmet) is an emission nebula in the constellation Canis Major. The nebula is approximately 11.96 thousand light years away and 30 light-years in size. It is also known as Sharpless 2-298, Gum 4 and RCW 5. Image includes IC468, PGC149790, PGC77049, PGC136794, LBN 1041, LBN 1040', 'ngc2359_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '109.625801870202', '-13.229034090175', '0.671002681396', '0.698040749775', '4185.714726545490', '2781.977117065982', '69.761912109092', '46.366285284433', '181.780192568106', 'y'),
('sh2-280', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sh2 280', '', '', 'LBN 970', '', 'Sh2 280', 'sh2-280.jpg', 'sh2-280_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'S:H:O 100:100:85 min @ 5 min exposures @-10C Total 4:45', 'Donvale', '2026-01-20', 'Sh2 280 is a rarely imaged faint emission nebula situated around 5500 light years away. It''s located very close to the Rosette Nebula. Processed as SHO.', 'sh2-280_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '98.581114590542', '2.536501987778', '0.670933253270', '0.697063433946', '4177.901368110860', '2781.018334803198', '69.631689468514', '46.350305580053', '181.806195093842', 'y'),
('sh2-284', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sh2 284', '', '', 'LBN 983', '', 'Sh2 284', 'sh2-284.jpg', 'sh2-284_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'S:H:O 100:100:100 min @ 5 min exposures @-10C Total 5:00', 'Donvale', '2026-01-22', 'Sh2-284 also know as LBN 983 is located 15,000 light-years away in the constellation Monoceros. Processed as SHO.', 'sh2-284_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '101.257096234372', '0.227964169707', '0.671345229844', '0.696146544920', '4169.725222563966', '2781.383287245614', '69.495420376066', '46.356388120760', '1.698576722944', 'y'),
('rcw075', '', '', '', '', 'RCW 75', '', '', 'Gum 48a', '', '', 'RCW 75 (Gum 48a) Stock 16', 'rcw75.jpg', 'rcw75_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'STL-11000M', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'SHO 90:90:95 mins @ 5 min exposures @-10C Total 4:35', 'Donvale', '2026-01-25', 'RCW 75 (also called Gum 48a) is  H II region in Centaurus. Distance is 6200 light years. Contains Stock 16 which is a very young Galactic open cluster.\r\n', 'rcw75_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '54.241293927431', '-23.312074554453', '1.545890701832', '1.609729086556', '9643.266198026411', '6429.359428918218', '160.721103300440', '107.155990481970', '215.106321058619', 'y'),
('ngc3293d', '', '', 'NGC 3293', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'NGC 3293', 'ngc3293d.jpg', 'ngc3293d_thumb.jpg', 'Open Cluster', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'SHO 180:200:185 @5min exposures total 9:25 @-10C', 'Donvale', '2026-02-03', 'NGC 3293 is an open cluster in the Carina constellation. It consists of more than 100 stars brighter than 14th magnitude in a 10 arc minute field. NGC 3293 is associated with the open cluster NGC 3324. Both are fairly young, at around 12 million years old. Taken over sereval nights.', 'ngc3293d_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '158.969740936646', '-58.230291760784', '0.671114132990', '0.689009986571', '4116.614091762082', '2768.345798584707', '68.610234862701', '46.139096643078', '181.902240467845', 'y'),
('sh2-297', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sh2 297', '', '', 'LBN 1039', '', 'Sh2 297', 'sh2-297.jpg', 'sh2-297_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'S:H:O 100:110:95 min @ 5 min exposures @-10C Total 5:05', 'Donvale', '2026-02-02', 'Sh2-284 also known as LBN 1039 is an emission nebula in the constellation Canis Major. Distance is estimated at 3,900 ly. Processed as SHO.', 'sh2-297_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '106.305017106635', '-12.318554894215', '0.671000594268', '0.697624580644', '4181.675703478346', '2782.639464429509', '69.694595057972', '46.377324407158', '2.099006889027', 'y'),
('ldn1634', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sh2 278', '', '', 'LDN 1634', '', 'LDN 1634 Sh2 278', 'ldn1634.jpg', 'ldn1634_thumb.jpg', 'Nebula', 'ASI2600MM DUO', 'AT12 IN', 'Paramount ME', 'Selfguide', 'S:H:O 175:190:180 min @ 5 min exposures @-10C Total 9:05', 'Donvale', '2026-02-03', 'SH2-278 is an emission nebula in constellation Orion. Image also includes LDN 1634 and LBN 960.', 'ldn1634_annotated.jpg', '3 KORRW', '79.941249521178', '-5.868776593661', '0.670995852125', '0.694440668198', '4163.529262434289', '2768.528885866862', '69.392154373905', '46.142148097781', '182.281416791196', 'y'),
